  1274	      <tr>
  1275	        <td><strong>LLaMA-2-7B-chat</strong></td>
  1276	        <td>Core language model for activation extraction and steered generation</td>
  1277	        <td>Same model used in the StyleVector paper. Results are directly comparable.</td>
  1278	      </tr>
  1279	      <tr>
  1280	        <td><strong>Gemini API (Flash)</strong></td>
  1281	        <td>Style-agnostic headline generation (Step 1 of StyleVector)</td>
  1282	        <td>Fast, free-tiered, and robust. Paper shows generic model choice has minimal impact on results.</td>
  1283	      </tr>
  1284	      <tr>
  1285	        <td><strong>Kaggle T4 GPU</strong></td>
  1286	        <td>Heavy compute: activation extraction, style vector training</td>
  1287	        <td>Free 16GB VRAM, sufficient for 4-bit quantized LLaMA-2-7B. Personal GPU (4GB) is insufficient.</td>
  1288	      </tr>
  1289	      <tr>
  1290	        <td><strong>Lightning AI</strong></td>
  1291	        <td>Overflow compute when Kaggle sessions expire</td>
  1292	        <td>~50 credits available. Used for long-running jobs that exceed Kaggle's session limit.</td>
  1293	      </tr>
  1294	      <tr>
  1295	        <td><strong>FastAPI</strong></td>
  1296	        <td>Backend REST API</td>
  1297	        <td>Fast, modern, Pydantic-native. Ideal for ML inference serving.</td>
  1298	      </tr>
  1299	      <tr>
  1300	        <td><strong>Next.js 14</strong></td>
  1301	        <td>Frontend application</td>
  1302	        <td>React-based with server components. Good Tailwind support. Auto-deploys on Vercel.</td>
  1303	      </tr>
  1304	      <tr>
  1305	        <td><strong>HuggingFace Spaces</strong></td>
  1306	        <td>Backend deployment</td>
  1307	        <td>Free tier, Docker-native, publicly accessible URL. Perfect for academic demos.</td>
  1308	      </tr>
  1309	      <tr>
  1310	        <td><strong>GitHub Actions</strong></td>
  1311	        <td>CI/CD pipeline</td>
  1312	        <td>Native GitHub integration, free for public repos, supports secret management for HF token.</td>
  1313	      </tr>
  1314	      <tr>
  1315	        <td><strong>Claude Code</strong></td>
  1316	        <td>Code writing, debugging, refactoring throughout project</td>
  1317	        <td>Best available tool for Python/FastAPI/Next.js code generation and debugging.</td>
  1318	      </tr>
  1319	    </tbody>
  1320	  </table>
  1321	</div>
  1322	
