  bullet("Baseline 2: RAG (BM25) — retrieve k=3 most similar past articles by the author using BM25. Provide as context in the prompt. Simple retrieval-based personalisation."),
  bullet("Baseline 3: Vanilla StyleVector — standard contrastive activation extraction and steering, without cold-start. Shows degradation on sparse authors."),
  bullet("Proposed: Cold-Start StyleVector — vanilla StyleVector for rich authors, cold-start vector for sparse authors. The key result is that this method performs well in both groups."),

  h2("9.3 Cross-Cultural Evaluation"),
  para("As an additional finding, the full evaluation pipeline is also run on the Indian dataset (TOI + HT journalists). This tests whether style clusters learned from Western journalism generalise to Indian journalistic styles. If they do, this significantly strengthens the contribution. If they do not, this is itself a valid research finding about the cultural specificity of journalistic style vectors."),

  new Paragraph({ children: [new PageBreak()] }),

  // ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
